## Exercise 9: Observe Password Status in /etc/shadow

### User without password

```bash
useradd nopassuser
grep nopassuser /etc/shadow
```

Expected:

```text
!!
```

---

### User with password

```bash
passwd nopassuser
grep nopassuser /etc/shadow
```

Expected:

```text
$6$xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
```

(Encrypted password)

---

### Lock the password

```bash
passwd -l nopassuser
grep nopassuser /etc/shadow
```

Expected:

```text
!$6$xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
```

or

```text
!!$6$xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
```

